[
    {
        "text": "Hi, I’m Francis, ",
        "start": 5.566,
        "duration": 1.4
    },
    {
        "text": "the host of this show \"Cooking with Dog.\"",
        "start": 6.966,
        "duration": 3.185
    },
    {
        "text": "Today, we will be making delicious Clam Chowder with seasonal clams and lots of vegetables.",
        "start": 10.85,
        "duration": 6.599
    },
    {
        "text": "To help de-sand, allow the clams to sit in about 3 percent salt water for 2 hours.",
        "start": 18.869,
        "duration": 5.243
    },
    {
        "text": "First, let’s cook the clams.",
        "start": 24.693,
        "duration": 2.835
    },
    {
        "text": "Place the clams into a bowl ",
        "start": 28.128,
        "duration": 2.834
    },
    {
        "text": "and scrub the shells in water, removing the sands.",
        "start": 31.603,
        "duration": 4.495
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, rinse them under running water.",
        "start": 40.466,
        "duration": 3.662
    },
    {
        "text": "Place the clams in a pot.",
        "start": 48.834,
        "duration": 2.669
    },
    {
        "text": "Add the white wine or sake ",
        "start": 53.865,
        "duration": 3.172
    },
    {
        "text": "and 200ml of water.",
        "start": 57.037,
        "duration": 3.5
    },
    {
        "text": "Cover and bring it to a boil on medium heat.",
        "start": 62.019,
        "duration": 5.303
    },
    {
        "text": "Boil the clams until all the shells are open.",
        "start": 73.442,
        "duration": 4.185
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, strain them with a mesh strainer ",
        "start": 80.991,
        "duration": 2.972
    },
    {
        "text": "covered with a paper towel.",
        "start": 83.963,
        "duration": 2.784
    },
    {
        "text": "Reserve the broth and place the clams onto a plate.",
        "start": 89.718,
        "duration": 4.834
    },
    {
        "text": "To help avoid drying, cover the plate with plastic wrap.",
        "start": 96.185,
        "duration": 5.203
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, let’s make the clam chowder.",
        "start": 101.942,
        "duration": 3.198
    },
    {
        "text": "In a pot, place the garlic ",
        "start": 105.356,
        "duration": 2.735
    },
    {
        "text": "and bacon.",
        "start": 110.229,
        "duration": 1.814
    },
    {
        "text": "Pour in the olive oil.  ",
        "start": 113.838,
        "duration": 2.504
    },
    {
        "text": "Turn on the burner and stir-fry the ingredients.",
        "start": 118.219,
        "duration": 3.989
    },
    {
        "text": "When the aroma grows stronger, ",
        "start": 128.1,
        "duration": 2.588
    },
    {
        "text": "add the onion, ",
        "start": 130.688,
        "duration": 1.718
    },
    {
        "text": "carrot ",
        "start": 134.44,
        "duration": 1.949
    },
    {
        "text": "and potato.",
        "start": 138.209,
        "duration": 1.934
    },
    {
        "text": "To help the vegetables cook evenly, ",
        "start": 140.446,
        "duration": 2.627
    },
    {
        "text": "the carrot is cut into slightly smaller pieces ",
        "start": 143.073,
        "duration": 3.168
    },
    {
        "text": "than the onion and potato.",
        "start": 146.241,
        "duration": 3.017
    },
    {
        "text": "Thoroughly stir-fry the vegetables ",
        "start": 149.258,
        "duration": 2.352
    },
    {
        "text": "but be careful not to burn them.",
        "start": 151.61,
        "duration": 2.8
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, reduce the heat to low.",
        "start": 155.243,
        "duration": 2.868
    },
    {
        "text": "And add the cake flour or all purpose flour.",
        "start": 159.197,
        "duration": 3.95
    },
    {
        "text": "Stir-fry until the flour is combined.",
        "start": 165.282,
        "duration": 3.969
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, pour in the clam broth.",
        "start": 172.476,
        "duration": 3.293
    },
    {
        "text": "And add the bay leaf.",
        "start": 177.304,
        "duration": 2.634
    },
    {
        "text": "Turn up the heat ",
        "start": 181.54,
        "duration": 1.968
    },
    {
        "text": "and thoroughly mix from the bottom.",
        "start": 183.508,
        "duration": 3.35
    },
    {
        "text": "Cover and simmer for 5 to 6 minutes.",
        "start": 190.594,
        "duration": 4.151
    },
    {
        "text": "When the broth thickens, ",
        "start": 196.164,
        "duration": 1.833
    },
    {
        "text": "it will easily burn so occasionally stir the ingredients.",
        "start": 197.997,
        "duration": 4.603
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, add the cabbage leaves ",
        "start": 208.568,
        "duration": 2.625
    },
    {
        "text": "and submerge them in the broth.",
        "start": 211.193,
        "duration": 2.549
    },
    {
        "text": "Cover and boil for 5 more minutes ",
        "start": 219.979,
        "duration": 2.679
    },
    {
        "text": "until the cabbage softens.",
        "start": 222.658,
        "duration": 2.758
    },
    {
        "text": "Mmmmm. It looks so delicious, doesn’t it?",
        "start": 226.784,
        "duration": 4.454
    },
    {
        "text": "Pour in the milk.",
        "start": 232.653,
        "duration": 2.2
    },
    {
        "text": "And add the salt ",
        "start": 239.039,
        "duration": 1.966
    },
    {
        "text": "and black pepper.",
        "start": 241.874,
        "duration": 3.914
    },
    {
        "text": "Heat the ingredients and mix again.",
        "start": 248.744,
        "duration": 3.433
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, remove the bay leaf.",
        "start": 254.145,
        "duration": 2.987
    },
    {
        "text": "Add the clams ",
        "start": 259.68,
        "duration": 2.086
    },
    {
        "text": "and the butter.",
        "start": 263.817,
        "duration": 2.084
    },
    {
        "text": "When the clams warm up, turn off the burner.",
        "start": 270.253,
        "duration": 4.119
    },
    {
        "text": "Ladle the clam chowder into a bowl.",
        "start": 279.775,
        "duration": 3.283
    },
    {
        "text": "Finally, sprinkle on the parsley leaves.",
        "start": 288.246,
        "duration": 4.023
    },
    {
        "text": "This clam chowder has a relatively fluid consistency, ",
        "start": 292.996,
        "duration": 4.086
    },
    {
        "text": "giving it a light taste.",
        "start": 297.082,
        "duration": 2.484
    },
    {
        "text": "Adding a small amount of butter at the last moment ",
        "start": 299.566,
        "duration": 3.445
    },
    {
        "text": "will brings out the aroma and the flavor.",
        "start": 303.011,
        "duration": 3.259
    },
    {
        "text": "The savory umami of the clams and vegetables brings out the flavor of the broth. Delicious!",
        "start": 306.271,
        "duration": 4.109
    },
    {
        "text": "Boil the potato until slightly crumbly ",
        "start": 315.574,
        "duration": 2.909
    },
    {
        "text": "so that the soup will be smooth and delicious.",
        "start": 318.483,
        "duration": 3.599
    },
    {
        "text": "Good luck in the kitchen!",
        "start": 322.082,
        "duration": 1.83
    }
]